    <stitle>FULL POWER HYDRAULIC ABS BRAKE SYSTEM - SPECIFICATIONS - FULL POWER BRAKE SYSTEM SPECIFICATIONS</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc id="hl04048702" svcproctype="describe" graphiccount="1">
        <title>FULL POWER BRAKE SYSTEM SPECIFICATIONS</title>
        <table id="t0404805" tblwidth="pg-wide">
            <title>Full Power Brake System Specifications</title>
            <tgroup cols="2" colsep="1" rowsep="0">
                <colspec colname="1" colwidth="3.49in"/>
                <colspec colname="2" colwidth="3.09in"/>
                <spanspec namest="1" nameend="2" spanname="1to2"/>
                <thead>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">ITEM</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2" align="center">
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">SPECIFICATION</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </thead>
                <tbody>
                    <row>
                        <entry colname="1">
                            <para>Brake Fluid Type</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry colname="2">
                            <para>DOT 3 or DOT 4</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Brake Fluid Quantity (Complete System)</para>
                            <para>
                                <emph type="bold">NOTE: Quantity varies according to vehicle wheelbase.</emph>
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>6.0 to 6.6 liters (12.7 to 13.9 pints)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Brake Fluid Quantity (Master Cylinder Reservoir to MAX mark)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>2.4 liters (5.1 pints)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Brake Fluid Quantity (HCU Reservoir)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1.7 liters (3.6 pints)</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Lubricant (wheel speed sensors only)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Mineral oil based and must contain molydisulfide. It should have excellent
                                anti-corrosion and adhesion characteristics. Must be capable of continuous function from
                                -40&#176; to 300&#176;F (-40&#176; to 150&#176;C)
                            </para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Park Brake Stroke (Measured at SAHR Canister)</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>1.5 &#177;0.25 inches</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Accumulator Pump Turn On Pressure</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>approx. 1770 psi</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>Accumulator Pump Turn Off Pressure</para>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>approx. 2320 psi</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                    <row>
                        <entry>
                            <para>System Voltage (Ignition ON), Measured at the following points:</para>
                            <seqlist>
                                <item>
                                    <para>31 Pin Connector</para>
                                    <randlist type="bullet">
                                        <item>
                                            <para>Pin 1 to pin 6 (gnd)</para>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                            <para>Pin 16 to pin 18 (gnd)</para>
                                        </item>
                                        <item>
                                            <para>Pin 17 to pin 19 (gnd)</para>
                                        </item>
                                    </randlist>
                                </item>
                                <item>
                                    <para>2 Pin Connector</para>
                                    <randlist type="bullet">
                                        <item>
                                            <para>Pin 2 to pin 1 (gnd)</para>
                                        </item>
                                    </randlist>
                                </item>
                            </seqlist>
                        </entry>
                        <entry>
                            <para>10 to 16 Vdc</para>
                        </entry>
                    </row>
                </tbody>
            </tgroup>
        </table>
        <para>
            <title>
                <emph type="bold">TIRE SIZE RANGE</emph>
            </title>
            For proper hydraulic ABS operation, front and rear tire sizes must be within 16% of each other. Do not use a
            tire size range that exceeds 16%. Calculate the tire size range with the equation in
            <hotlnk xrefid="f0404872">FIGURE 78</hotlnk>.
        </para>
        <figure id="f0404872" figsize="pg-wide">
            <graphic id="g0404872" filename="../figg04/G0404872.webp" type="webp" scalefit="1" scalefitwidth="514px"
                     scalefitheight="112px"/>
            <caption>Figure 78. Formula for Calculating Tire Size Range</caption>
        </figure>
